voices.mp3Text: Look on the bright side Alchemist: you can make yourself a potion to forget this fight.
voices.name: Alchemist

voices.mp3Text: Alchemist, you could be riding that frost dragon and I'd still end you.
voices.name: Alchemist

voices.mp3Text: You think you're the first spirit I've dealt with?
voices.name: Ancient Apparition

voices.mp3Text: For someone who says he's anti-magic you sure like teleporting around the battle field.
voices.name: Anti-Mage

voices.mp3Text: Anti-Mage, beating hypocrites like you never gets old.
voices.name: Anti-Mage

voices.mp3Text: Arc Warden, I'll take you seriously the moment you start talking in the first person.
voices.name: Arc Warden

voices.mp3Text: I hope Goodkind is taking notes, because people are gonna love reading about me killing you.
voices.name: Axe

voices.name: Bane

voices.name: Bane

voices.name: Batrider

voices.mp3Text: Out of the way, vermin!
voices.name: Batrider

voices.mp3Text: No one is my master!
voices.name: Beastmaster

voices.mp3Text: This forest belongs to me!
voices.name: Beastmaster

voices.mp3Text: You don't need to hunt me down, I'm right here.

voices.mp3Text: The only blood being spilt here is yours.

voices.mp3Text: I'm one bounty you're never cashing in.
voices.name: Bounty Hunter

voices.mp3Text: I know a thing or two about drunken masters; and you my friend, are just the town lush.
voices.name: Brewmaster

voices.mp3Text: The beating Tusk gave you will feel like a sweet memory when I'm done with you.
voices.name: Bristleback

voices.mp3Text: It's over between us Arachnia!
voices.name: Broodmother

voices.mp3Text: because you never fought me.

voices.mp3Text: Die, slaver!

voices.mp3Text: Oh, shut up.

voices.mp3Text: Not even the Siren could protect you.

voices.mp3Text: Enunciate!
voices.name: Spectre

voices.mp3Text: Stupid cow.

voices.mp3Text: You'll have to try harder than that Storm Spirit.

voices.mp3Text: No one likes you, Techies. Just go away.

voices.mp3Text: Saved you the trouble. Idiots.

voices.mp3Text: You should've stuck to the library, Lanaya.

voices.mp3Text: will have to find a new errand girl.

voices.mp3Text: I made a bet with Kunkka that I'd bag you first.
voices.name: Tidehunter

voices.mp3Text: Ever wondered if maybe your city had it comin', Rizzrack?

voices.mp3Text: The trees have been saying some very bad things about you, Timbersaw.

voices.mp3Text: The trees will be just fine without you.

voices.name: Treant Protector

voices.mp3Text: You got spirit Warlord, I'll give you that.

voices.mp3Text: Trolls. Always a challenge, never an obstacle.

voices.mp3Text: You threw your life away for a bet, Tusk? Oh! I like that.

voices.mp3Text: You wanted to fight in a war, Tusk? I give you war!

voices.mp3Text: Get back in your pit, Underlord.

voices.mp3Text: You've forgotten your life. None will remember your death.

voices.mp3Text: Let's if your poison's good for cleaning off blood.

voices.mp3Text: Traxex was right about you: you are a middling talent.

voices.mp3Text: , killed 'em all.

voices.mp3Text: And I'm taking your monkey friend with me.

voices.mp3Text: King? Ha!

voices.mp3Text: Get back up again, I dare you.

voices.mp3Text: You should have turned yourself into swan and hid, you bastard.

voices.mp3Text: , Io.

voices.mp3Text: I'm just getting started!
First Blood! Ha! I'm just getting started.
First Blood! Well, today anyway.
Too easy.
First Blood! Well, not first blood, I've killed lots of people I just—well you get the idea.

voices.mp3Text: watching my back. There's a first time for everything.
